label: Barren Sparse Vegetation
comment: Lands exposed soil, sand, or rocks and has less than 10% vegetative cover during any time of the year.
explanation: Barren Sparse Vegetation: Lands exposed soil, sand, or rocks and has less than 10% vegetative cover during any time of the year.

label: Croplands
comment: Lands covered with temporary crops followed by harvest and a bare soil period (e.g., single and multiple cropping systems). Note that perennial woody crops will be classified as the appropriate forest or shrub land cover type.
explanation: Croplands: Lands covered with temporary crops followed by harvest and a bare soil period (e.g., single and multiple cropping systems). Note that perennial woody crops will be classified as the appropriate forest or shrub land cover type.

label: Closed Shrublands
comment: Lands with woody vegetation less than 2 meters tall and with shrub canopy cover >60%. The shrub foliage can be either evergreen or deciduous.
explanation: Closed Shrublands: Lands with woody vegetation less than 2 meters tall and with shrub canopy cover >60%. The shrub foliage can be either evergreen or deciduous.

label: Cropland/Natural Vegetation Mosaics
comment: Lands with a mosaic of croplands, forest, shrublands, and grasslands in which no one component comprises more than 60% of the landscape
explanation: Cropland/Natural Vegetation Mosaics: Lands with a mosaic of croplands, forest, shrublands, and grasslands in which no one component comprises more than 60% of the landscape

label: Deciduous Broadleaf Forests
comment: Lands dominated by woody vegetation with a percent cover >60% and height exceeding 2 meters.  Consists of broadleaf tree communities with an annual cycle of leaf-on and leaf-off periods.
explanation: Deciduous Broadleaf Forests: Lands dominated by woody vegetation with a percent cover >60% and height exceeding 2 meters.  Consists of broadleaf tree communities with an annual cycle of leaf-on and leaf-off periods.

label: Deciduous Needleleaf Forests
comment: Lands dominated by woody vegetation with a percent cover >60% and height exceeding 2 meters.  Consists of seasonal needleleaf tree communities with an annual cycle of leaf-on and leaf-off periods.
explanation: Deciduous Needleleaf Forests: Lands dominated by woody vegetation with a percent cover >60% and height exceeding 2 meters.  Consists of seasonal needleleaf tree communities with an annual cycle of leaf-on and leaf-off periods.

label: Evergreen Broadleaf Forests
comment: Lands dominated by woody vegetation with a percent cover >60% and height exceeding 2 meters. Almost all trees and shrubs remain green year round. Canopy is never without green foliage.
explanation: Evergreen Broadleaf Forests: Lands dominated by woody vegetation with a percent cover >60% and height exceeding 2 meters. Almost all trees and shrubs remain green year round. Canopy is never without green foliage.

label: Evergreen Needleleaf Forests
comment: Lands dominated by woody vegetation with a percent cover >60% and height exceeding 2 meters. Almost all trees remain green all year. Canopy is never without green foliage.
explanation: Evergreen Needleleaf Forests: Lands dominated by woody vegetation with a percent cover >60% and height exceeding 2 meters. Almost all trees remain green all year. Canopy is never without green foliage.

label: Grasslands brackish, or fresh water.
comment: Lands with herbaceous types of cover. Tree and shrub cover is less than 10%. Permanent wetlands lands with a permanent mixture of water and herbaceous or woody vegetation. The vegetation can be present in either salt, brackish, or fresh water.
explanation: Grasslands: Lands with herbaceous types of cover. Tree and shrub cover is less than 10%. Permanent wetlands lands with a permanent mixture of water and herbaceous or woody vegetation. The vegetation can be present in either salt, brackish, or fresh water.

label: Mixed Forests of landscape.
comment: Lands dominated by trees with a percent cover >60% and height exceeding 2 meters.  Consists of tree communities with interspersed mixtures or mosaics of the other four forest types.  None of the forest types exceeds 60% of landscape.
explanation: Mixed Forests: Lands dominated by trees with a percent cover >60% and height exceeding 2 meters.  Consists of tree communities with interspersed mixtures or mosaics of the other four forest types.  None of the forest types exceeds 60% of landscape.

label: Open Shrublands
comment: Lands with woody vegetation less than 2 meters tall and with shrub canopy cover between 10-60%. The shrub foliage can be either evergreen or deciduous.
explanation: Open Shrublands: Lands with woody vegetation less than 2 meters tall and with shrub canopy cover between 10-60%. The shrub foliage can be either evergreen or deciduous.

label: Savannas
comment: Lands with herbaceous and other understory systems, and with forest canopy cover between 10-30%. The forest cover height exceeds 2 meters.
explanation: Savannas: Lands with herbaceous and other understory systems, and with forest canopy cover between 10-30%. The forest cover height exceeds 2 meters.

label: Snow and Ice
comment: Lands under snow/ice cover most of the year.
explanation: Snow and Ice: Lands under snow/ice cover most of the year.

label: Urban and Built-Up Lands
comment: Land covered by buildings and other man-made structures.
explanation: Urban and Built-Up Lands: Land covered by buildings and other man-made structures.

label: Permanent Wetlands
comment: Lands with a permanent mixture of water and herbaceous or woody vegetation that cover extensive areas. The vegetation can be present in either salt, brackish, or fresh water
explanation: Permanent Wetlands: Lands with a permanent mixture of water and herbaceous or woody vegetation that cover extensive areas. The vegetation can be present in either salt, brackish, or fresh water

label: Woody Savannas
comment: Lands with herbaceous and other understory systems, and with forest canopy cover between 30-60%. The forest cover height exceeds 2 meters.
explanation: Woody Savannas: Lands with herbaceous and other understory systems, and with forest canopy cover between 30-60%. The forest cover height exceeds 2 meters.

comment: Site is flat with no significant land surface changes
explanation: Site is flat with no significant land surface changes

comment: Site is in a valley, with slopes all around
explanation: Site is in a valley, with slopes all around

label: Flat
comment: The site is flat and the exposure is not in any specific direction
explanation: The site is flat and the exposure is not in any specific direction
